videos.title: Exploring Chintamani Temple, Theur - A Spiritual Journey.
videos.description:
The Chintamani Temple of Theur is a Hindu temple dedicated to the Supreme God Ganesha according to the Ganapatya, situated 25 km (16 mi) from Pune, of the Ashtavinayaka the eight revered shrines of Ganesha in the Indian state of Maharashtra is considered larger and famous.

The legends of the temple are as below: how Bhagwan Ganesh got the wish to give a jewel Chintamani for his devotee the sage Kapila by defeating the greedy king Gana and how he allayed the disturbed mind of the god Brahma who meditated on him in Theur. This temple is related to the Ganapatya saint Morya Gosavi who beholds from the period 13-17 AD. On the one hand, according to ancient legends, the temple existed from time immemorial, on the other hand, nowadays the shape of the temple was constructed by him or by his heir. The Chintamani Temple was also a religious centre of attraction to the Peshwa rulers more so in Madhavrao I (17451772) since he added a touch on the structural design of this temple.

Though Theur is taken as the fifth temple to be visited in the Ashtavinayak circuit trail, people prefer to visit Theur immediately after Morgaon which is convenient for them.

videos.title: Take a look at one of finest temple's of Pune I Maharashtra.
videos.description:
Ranjangaon Mahaganpati Temple one of the finest temple based in Pune, Maharashtra. Located in a peaceful village of Ranjangaon, this is one of the Ashtavinayak; the eight sacred temples of Lord Ganesha in Maharashtra. Housed in a temple, which is said to have been built in the 9th or 10th century, the temple today boasts of great architectural designs, which enthral visitors through carved patterns.

The sanctum of the temple contains the splendid and striking statue of Lord Mahaganpati with ten heads and twenty arms portraying absolute control ad godliness. The form of Ganesha associated with this idol is considered to be the most powerful and people use it to pray for success and to help them overcome every hurdle that they may come across.

The temple is located surrounded by beautiful sceneries and thus attracts both the devotees and visitors seeking for inner peace.

videos.title: All you need to know about Mulshi Dam, Pune I Maharashtra.
videos.description:
Located in the Sahyadri mountain range, Mulshi Dam in Pune, Maharashtra, is another gateway that is associated with calmness and beautiful sceneries. This dam has been constructed over the Mula River and its main use is to generate hydroelectric power. There is the availability of green vegetation, waterfalls, and natural scenery, therefore acting as an added advantage to the lovers of nature and photographers. The tourists can also engage in boat cruises, and nature walks, sighting birds among other things. Mulshi is again a good place for a silent picnic in the lap of nature. Several tourist destinations are based within a short distance; these are the Tamini Ghat and the beautiful village of Mulshi. For buffs, for those, who love to go on adventurous trips, for those, who need a break from busy and noisy city life, Mulshi Dam is just a perfect place.

videos.title: Discovering the Immaculate Conception Church: A Panjim, Goa Landmark I India.
videos.description:
A warm welcome to the Church of Immaculate Conception, Panjim, Goa! This beautiful Baroque-style church, built first in 1541 and then rebuilt in 1619 after a series of fires, manifests the rich tradition left behind by the Portuguese. The brilliant white faade and grand double-flight of stairs are prominent on a hilltop, giving a panoramic view of Panjim town. The church is devoted to Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception, having grand and elegant exuding altars, with the principal among them being under Mary Immaculate. This tower belongs to the church that houses the second largest bell present in Goa. So, just relax as we take you through the history, architecture, and spiritual significance of this iconic landmark.
 Do not forget to like, share, and subscribe for more travel and cultural insight!

Join us for a tranquil visit to one of Karnataka's celebrated tourist destinations, perfect for photography, relaxation, and local shopping. Subscribe for more incredible Indian destinations!

videos.title: Exploring the Majestic Maratha Stronghold I Torna Fort I Pune.
videos.description:
Torna fort also called as Prachandagad is a huge fort situated in the district of Pune in the state of Maharashtra in India. It remains culturally important due to the fact that this was the very first fort Shivaji I captured, at the young age of 16 in the year 1646.

This fort is reported to have been built by the Shiva Panth in the early part of the 13th century. There is a temple of Menghai Devi also known as the Tornaji temple close to the entrance of the fort. This fort was taken by Malik Ahmed a Bahamani ruler in the year 586 AH, i.e. during the time of Alauddin Khilji in late 1470s.

The distance of the fort is approximately fifty kilometers using Pabe Ghat and lies to the southwest of Pune in the Western Ghat of Sahyadri mountain ranges with the starting point at Velhe village.

videos.title: CST to Gateway of India | 360 Street View | 8K | VR
videos.description:
Presenting an 8K Virtual Reality (VR)360 Streetview of Mumbai - the City of Dreams of India.

Today we know Mumbai as the commercial and financial hub of India, a sprawling metropolis spread over a huge area. But originally it was a group of 7 islands namely Bombay, Mahim, Parel, Worli, Mazgaon, Old Womans Island, or Little Colaba and Colaba. The Koli people were indigenous to the area and mostly involved in fishing activities. The group of islands came under Portuguese control in 1534 CE, later in 1672 CE, the islands came under the British East India company. 
Colaba is the southernmost island and is one of the most famous parts of Mumbai owing to the presence of the iconic Gateway of India along with a host of other famous buildings. The Portuguese and British influences are still quite visible even after so many centuries in the colonial and gothic buildings which are well preserved. Today Colaba is a bustling district of south Mumbai and is an eclectic mix of art, culture, fashion, food, and commerce, so much so that it is known as the Culture square of Mumbai.

What is Virutal Reality?
Virtual reality (VR) is a computer-generated scenario that simulates a realistic experience. The immersive environment can be similar to the real world in order to create a lifelike experience grounded in reality or sci-fi. Augmented reality systems may also be considered a form of VR that layers virtual information over a live camera feed into a headset, or through a smartphone or tablet device.

What is 360 Degree Video?
360-degree videos, also known as immersive videos or spherical videos, are video recordings where a view in every direction is recorded at the same time, shot using an omnidirectional camera or a collection of cameras. During playback the viewer has control of the viewing direction like a panorama.

videos.title: Shad Suk Mynsiem Festival | Meghalaya | 360 Experience Immersing in the Vibrant Celebrations | VR.
videos.description:
Welcome to this 360 immersive experience of the vibrant Shad Suk Mynsiem Festival! This festival is celebrated annually by the Khasi tribe in Meghalaya, India to mark the harvest season and to pray for a bountiful crop in the upcoming year.

As you watch this video, you'll be transported to the heart of the celebrations, where you'll witness the Khasi tribe members dressed in their traditional attire, dancing to the beat of the drums and other musical instruments. You'll also see the stunningly decorated streets and buildings, and witness the vibrant colors and intricate designs of the traditional clothing worn by the festival participants.

This 360 experience will take you on a journey through the various rituals and customs of the festival, including the sacrificial offering of a goat, and the symbolic washing of the village square, known as "Ka Iew Luri Lura". You'll also see the "Dance of the Priestesses", a unique and mesmerizing performance by young Khasi girls, believed to be the embodiment of goddesses.

So sit back, relax, and let this immersive experience take you on a journey through the lively and colorful world of the Shad Suk Mynsiem Festival. Don't forget to adjust your screen settings to fully experience the 360 view!

videos.title: Take look at one of the most sacred and spiritual Ballaleshwar Ashtavinayak I Pali I Maharashtra
videos.description:
Welcome to the holy yatra of Ballaleshwar Ashtavinayak, located in a peaceful village called Pali in Raigad, Maharashtra! One of the eight sacred Ashtavinayak temples exists here and is dedicated to Lord Ganesha, very close to the hearts of people who believe in him. This temple was named after a devoted young boy, Ballal, whose undying faith in Ganesh led to his coming to life. This shrine has been hallowed by devotion and divine magic.

This temple architecture is one of the best examples of Maratha style, consisting of various carvings and displays regarding ingenuity in its design: using sunlight; it lights up the idol during early morning hours. Ballaleshwar Ganesha is an idol with a different style of sitting on a throne studded with diamonds at the eyes and navel. The temple complex contains a beautiful bell brought from a church in Portugal, thus making the temple complex more historical.

This wondrous temple is enveloped by greenery and serenading landscapes, ideally apt for meditation and prayer. Ganesh Chaturthi, with all its pomp, comes here as the festival and receives thousands of devotees from all over the country every year.

It is considered as the first out of eight Ashtavinayak, idols and is a prominent place of pilgrimage for devotees from all over the world. One of the monument of Culture, the temple is architectural marvel which is built with black stones and has four gates that denote the four Yugas, the temple dates back to the 14 century. Inside the sanctum sanctorum there is the Mayureshwar idol that has the hood of a cobra and the Lord is depicted to be riding a peacock. Due to the significant history and spirituality that Preah Vihear Temple carries with it, the temple together with the surrounding environment invoke blessing and peacefulness among the visitors.

videos.title: Take a look at the living root bridge in, Riwai village I Meghalaya
videos.description:
Here is one of the most mysteriously beautiful village named Riwai in Meghalaya and the hidden beauty of Mother Nature  the Living Root Bridge! This magnificent site has been developed from the ingenious expertise of the Khasi tribe of the Meghalaya state, who have been keeping up these tree houses for generations. By only allowing the aerial roots of the Ficus elastica tree to stretch over the water bodies, they have constructed strong, living bridges that can withstand harsh conditions and times.

As you approach the bridge on the grassy trails, one is bound to marvel at the natural endowment of this rich, verdant region-Meghalaya. For those who may argue that such structures are man-made and not natural, well the Living Root Bridge at Riwai symbolizes much more than just engineering advancement  it symbolizes an understanding of what it means to be a living soul on this earth, a dwelling part of a living ecosystem. Immerse yourself into the calm and the bits of rustic beauty that are situated in this natural landscape and learn about the Khasi tribes as well.

videos.title: Take a look at the magnificent Somnath Temple I Gujarat.
videos.description:
Somnath temple is one of the significant and oldest temples of Lord Shiva situated at Prabhas Patan near Veraval in Gujarat. This shrine is considered as the first of the twelve Jyotirlinga shrines of Shiva. Arguably, the temple has been destroyed and rebuilt severally, which attributes to the concept of the fight of faith. The present building was built in 1951 and it has got the Chalukyan style of architecture carved and giant stone shikhara. The other site to see in the temple complex is the Somnath Museum, sound and light show, and Prabhas Patan Museum, to understand the evolution and importance of the place.

videos.title: Bibi Ka Maqbara: India's Mini Taj Mahal | Maharashtra
videos.description:
Welcome to our tour of Bibi Ka Maqbara, an amazing monument from the Mughal era located in Chhatrapati Sambhaji Nagar, Maharashtra! Bibi Ka Maqbara, often referred to as the ""Taj of Deccan"", is a magnificent mausoleum built by Mughal Emperor Aurangzeb's son, Azzam Shah, in memory of his mother Dilras Banu Begum, also known as Rabia-ud-Daurani. The monument, which was completed in 1678, bears a striking resemblance to the Taj Mahal and showcases magnificent Mughal architecture.

Set against a backdrop of lush green landscape, the white marble mausoleum is decorated with intricate carvings and delicate floral designs. The large central dome, surrounded by four elegant minarets, creates a picturesque silhouette against the sky. Tranquil gardens, reflecting pools and pathways enhance the beauty of the monument and offer visitors a peaceful retreat.

Join us as we explore the historical and architectural significance of Bibi Ka Maqbara, delve into its rich past and the art that makes it a must-see destination in Maharashtra. Don't forget to like, share and subscribe for more incredible historical journeys!

videos.title: National War Memorial, New Delhi.
videos.description:
The National War Memorial is an Indian national monument built to honor and remember soldiers of the Indian military who fought in armed conflicts of Independent India. The names of armed forces personnel killed during the armed conflicts with Pakistan and China as well as the 1961 War in Goa, Operation Pawan, and other operations such as Operation Rakshak are inscribed on the memorial walls in golden letters.

This monument is spread over 40 acres of land and was built by the Government of India around the existing chhatri, near India Gate, New Delhi. The memorial wall is flushed with the ground and in harmony with existing aesthetics. It completed in January 2019 and was unveiled on 25 February 2019 in an inauguration ceremony held at the monument where the Prime Minister of India in the presence of CDS of India, and the 3 Chief of Staffs of Indian Armed Forces, ignited the eternal flame of Amar Jawan Jyoti (Flames of Eternal Soldiers) at Amar Chakra under the main obelisk of the monument.
The Memorial has four concentric circles and a central obelisk, at the bottom of which burns an 'eternal flame' representing the immortal soldier (Amar Jawan). The concentric circles are designed as a Chakravyuh, an ancient Indian war formation are called as follows

Amar Chakra (Circle of Immortality): This structure of the memorial derives its name from the Eternal Flame (Amar Jawan Jyoti), continuously burning under the main obelisk at the center of the monument. The flame symbolizes the immortality of the spirit of fallen soldiers and the promise that the Nation will never forget their sacrifices.
Veerta Chakra (Circle of Bravery): The second circle depicts the Bravery of Indian forces in the form of a covered gallery that exhibits six murals crafted in bronze depicting valiant battle actions of Indian Armed Forces. The battles showcased here are Battle of Gangasagar, Longewala, Tithwal, Rizangla, Operation Meghdoot and Operation Trident.
Tyag Chakra (Circle of Sacrifice): The circular concentric walls of honor, which symbolize the ancient war formation Chakravyuh. The walls are clad with granite tablets where an independent granite tablet is dedicated to each soldier who has made the supreme sacrifice in the battlefield, where his name is etched in golden letters along with the details of Rank.
Rakshak Chakra (Circle of Protection): The outermost circle made of rows of trees in the Rakshak Chakra is a reassurance to the citizens of the country about their safety against any threat, with each tree representing the soldiers who ensure the territorial integrity of the Nation, round the clock.
The Param Yodha Sthal houses the busts of all the 21 recipients of the Param Vir Chakra, India's highest military honour.

Located at Kvoorathu and spread over an area of 10 acres, Pathiramanal means Sands of the night. This backwater is easily accessible through boat from both Alappuzha and Kumarakom.

A number of birds particularly migratory birds can also be sighted within the island, thus qualifying it as an ideal place for bird watching. videos.title: Manipal University: A journey through nature innovation and oasis of knowledge
videos.description:
Manipal University, which is an excellent educational institution known for its academic achievements and advanced research, is situated in the coastal town of Manipal, Karnataka, India. The university was established in 1953 and has transformed into a global education Centre that attracts students from more than 60 different countries..

Manipal University was originally founded by Dr. T.M.A Pai as Manipal Institute of Technology (MIT) where the education revolution began in India. Over time, it diversified its field of study to become a multi-disciplinary university known as the Manipal Academy of Higher Education (MAHE).

Covering an area of 600 acres that combines modern architectural buildings with scenic beauty, it has all the necessary facilities for effective learning both within and outside academics.

Higher education is a beacon of light in Manipal University, where it mixes academic strictness and whole development. This distinguishes it from other institutions because of its innovation, global collaborations, and community engagement for students to thrive in an ever-advancing world. If a scholar or prospective student or even an academician, then Manipal University is the place to be with its ever-bustling atmosphere that creates a proper field for everyone who wishes to fulfil his dreams.

videos.title: International Centre Goa | Hotels of Goa | India
videos.description:
The International Centre Goa (ICG) is a non-profit autonomous society founded in June 1987, under the Societies Registration Act, 1860. It was inaugurated by His Excellency, the former President of India, late Dr. Shankar Dayal Sharma, on 18th June 1996. The Centre was conceived as a forum to bring together thinkers, scholars, academics, achievers, sociologists, industrialists and creative people from India and around the world.
Since inception, ICG has emerged as the hub of socio-cultural activities, political dialogue, economic debates and a variety of programmes ranging from film festivals, exhibitions, workshops, concerts, plays, to quiz, painting competitions and even social evenings. A minimum of 20,000 people annually visit the Centre for various reasons keeping the ambiance vibrant and lively.
What keeps ICG going is the diversity of the programmes organised on a regular basis. Talks and workshops on Journalism, Global Terrorism, Womens Reservation Bill, Good Governance, Pottery & Origami Workshops, Art Camps & Exhibits, Waste Management, Acting and Scriptwriting and National and International Seminars on subjects like Right to Information, Human Development, Coastal Regulation Zone Draft Policy, Goa Regional Plan, Women in Media, and The South Asia Media Summits are organised throughout.

Promoting culture is one of the Centres priorities and the reason for organizing the Goa Arts and Literary Festival. Unlike any other festival of its kind in India, the Goa festival has a strong local component, which showcases the rich art, music and literature of the state. Beyond the Goa focus, the festival seeks to highlight creative excellence across Indias literary landscape, the Goan Diaspora spread across the world with an emphasis on the newest emerging generations of writers and artists. The other cultural events organized in the past were the Dastkaari Haat Exhibition, Japanese Kite festival, Italian film and food festival etc.
Under its initiative Clean Goa for Green Goa, and I Care for Goa, ICG organizes activities and talks on environment, waste management, organic farming etc. Recycling units for waste management and a rainwater harvesting and groundwater recharging unit have also been set up in the Centres premises. ICG further plans to install Wind-Solar hybrid systems, to cater to most of the electrical power needs of the Centre.

videos.title: Welcome to Grishneshwar temple One of India's 12 jyotirlingas | Maharashtra
videos.description:
Welcome to our trip to Grishneshwar Temple, one of the twelve Jyotirlingas dedicated to Lord Shiva located in Chhatrapati Sambhaji Nagar, Maharashtra! Built of red basalt stone, this ancient temple is a masterpiece of Maratha temple architecture and has great spiritual significance. According to legend, this temple was built by Queen Ahilyabai Holkar in the 18th century, although its origins are much earlier.

The temple's intricate carvings depict various deities and mythological scenes, reflecting the rich craftsmanship of the period. The sanctum sanctorum houses the revered Jyotirlinga and the quiet atmosphere of the temple offers a peaceful retreat for worshipers and visitors alike. Grishneshwar temple has a beautiful courtyard and a sacred pool, enhancing the spiritual experience.

Join us as we explore the history, architecture and religious significance of the Grishneshwar temple, delving into the legends and traditions that make it a pilgrimage site. Don't forget to like, share and subscribe for more spiritual and cultural journey!

videos.description:
Welcome to Temghar Dam, one of the beautiful and serene places close to Pune in Maharashtra! Nestled in the heart of the lush green Western Ghats, Temghar Dam becomes a nature lovers' perfect getaway looking forward to enjoying peaceful time and getting away from hectic lives back in the city. This lovely dam is built across Mutha River and supplies quite a good quantity of water supply around its precincts.

Temghar Dam is a place with superb surroundings. The lush green hills, the dense forests, and the placid reservoir mirroring the sky like a glass are some of the characteristics that make this place ideal for picnics and nature walks. videos.title: Exploring Chunar Fort: The archaeological Gem of Uttar Pradesh
videos.description:
Chunar Fort is located in the div of Uttar Pradesh in India and it is an ancient fort build on the top of a hillock and overlooking the stream of the Ganga river. The first records of this place date back to the eleventh century, which means that this place is, indeed, historically very important. The fort has historical signification as through the time of Maurya and Gupta dynasties and Mughals Empires even up to the British colonization period. Structurally, it exhibits a unique combination of Hindu and Mughal style within an architectural diversity of giant gateways, and towers and subterranean passages. There is also the association with local folk lore, such as the story of the legendary King Vikramaditya who supposedly spent 14 weeks at the fort and the mystical saint, Bhartrihari, who is said to have resided in a cave on the fort. present day Chunar Fort is a testimonial to the historical heritage and Identity of Indias colonial history and has become an important destination for history lovers and travelers. The hill fortress for which it is famous offers spectacular views of the surrounding landscape besides having a rich history that makes it one of the most popular tourist attractions for the Uttar Pradesh region today.

videos.description: The town of Sanchi is renowned for its Buddhist Stupas, which are hemispherical structures containing relics of the Buddha or his disciples. This colonial structure has a number of paintings, sculpture and manuscripts displayed on the interior walls and within the rooms located within the museum. The memorial signifies the history of Kolkata and it is a structure created as a part of the legacy of the cultural richness of the country. Malik Mughits Mosque

Malik Mughits Mosque is one of the most significant historical and architectural landmarks in Mandu. This mosque portrays the common Islamic design found in Islamic constructions with its large domes, intricate carvings and big prayer halls. The mosque was named after Malik Mughith who was a nobleman from the Sultanate. Visitors are amazed by the mosques complex geometric patterns and inscriptions made on it that reveal the cultural diversity and religious evolution taking place within this area.

Dai Ki Choti Behen Ka Mahal

Another interesting structure is Dai Ki Choti Behen Ka Mahal meaning Palace of Wet Nurses Younger Sister in Mandu. It has exceptional architecture and historical importance among other palaces in Mandu. It was built for sister of wet nurse who played significant role to royal family. Despite being small compared to other palaces within Mandu, it is treasured because of its simple yet beautiful outlook that provides an environment full of tranquility.

 This huge fortified compound offered food, shelter as well as security for tired travelers together with their caravans on such journeys.

videos.title: Welcome to an engineering marvel, Panchakki I Chhatrapati Sambhaji Nagar I Maharashtra
videos.description:
Now, we will review one of the most fantastic engineering feats of the Panchakki of Chhatrapati Sambhaji Nagar, formerly known as Aurangabad, in Maharashtra. Also called the Water Mill, it represents a fantastically outstanding medieval Indian engineering feat. In this 17th-century era, the water mill was converted into a flour mill that supplied flour to pilgrims who visited the Dargah of Baba Shah Musafir by Turktaz Khana saint of the Sufi sect.

The water mill is powered by an underground water channel drawing its source from a spring several kilometers away in the mountains. Guided through intricate channels and under-ground pipes, the water reaches the mill to turn a large grinding stone. Such ingenuity as far as engineering goes this not only embodies highly developed engineering skills but also shows the practical application of hydraulic energy at work.

There are lush gardens and serene landscapes all around Panchakki, with a beautiful mosque and mesmerizing artificial waterfall that helps to add to the tranquil-like ambiance of the place. This place resembles the blending of spirituality and technological expertise of the Mughal era.

videos.title: Exploring the opulence of Pune's most famous Shaniwar wada I Pune I Maharashtra
videos.description:
Welcome to the intrinsic and historical fortress, the Shaniwar Wada, in the heart of Pune, Maharashtra! Envisioned and built-in 1732 by Bajirao I, this Peshwa of the Maratha Empire brought in the prestigious Shaniwar Wada to stand in all its pride and glory to proclaim its opulence and architectural genius. Constructed as a royal residence initially, this majestic fortress had some of the most important events of Indian history take place within its vicinities and still parades that chivalry of Maratha pride.

The Delhi Darwaza forms the entrance gate of this fort and has been made sturdy to take enemy attacks. Ruins of the royal palace, including the Diwan-e-Aam, or the public audience hall, and remains of the ground floor of existing buildings give one a view of how the royals lived. Gardens and fountains present inside the complex enhance its beauty and make it serene.

One of the main reasons Shaniwar Wada is so famous is its delicately intricate wooden architecture, with many beautifully carved pillars, graceful arches, and varieties of intricate latticework. Seven bastions and strong walls are testimony to its strategic importance in the past. Today, Shaniwar Wada is not only one of the favorite tourist spots but also a site that is abuzz with several light and sound shows and cultural programs and events that capture its rich history.

The time has come to take ourselves through the pages of time and explore all the great warriors of history, architectural brilliance, cultural significance, stories of bravery and  legacyShaniwar Wada. Please like, share, and subscribe for more such exciting journeys into history!




Contact us on connect@youtellme.ai

Discover the beauty of the Champa Baoli at Mandu in the state of Madhya Pradesh which reveals the latent potentials of ancient Indian structural design. Stepwell built during the reign of the Sultans of Malwa and part of the royal Jahaz Mahal complex, this is also known as the Champa scent stepwell. How it was constructed  with numerous layers and deep steps this architectural creation was used as a stepwell and a source of water, more importantly, it provided people with a place in which they could escape the heat during the summer. The fact that it is a multi-storied building had gracefully designed arches, steps which were symmetrical and underground chambers that kept the water cool adding to the ambience. It is believed that the cool breeze from the Baoli was aromatic, thus enhancing on the legend.

videos.description:
Join us for a tour through the majestic site of Ujala Baodi  a stepwell in the dimension of time, in the bewitching city of Mandu, Madhya Pradesh. This architectural marvel also known as the Bright Well is interesting in terms of functionality as well as art. It is the Mughal water supply system built to provide the surrounding region with water to quench its thirst and Ujala Baodi is a good example of this technique. Most of the step-wells that were constructed are symmetrical and this particular stepwell also has a well-carved structure with some very beautiful stone carvings which has won my heart, the environment is cooler than outside and the calmness of the place makes it perfect for enthusiasts on history and architecture.
Watch this video about the historical importance of Ujala Baodi to Mandu, its water supply system, and the beautiful architecture evident in this construct. The clear paths that we now follow are intact and I guarantee that nothing less than the history of pomp and past glory is written on the walls of this structure.

videos.description:

videos.title: Unveiling the Secrets of Mastani's Tomb in Pabal: A Historical Treasure Near Pune
videos.description:
Discover the hidden historical gem of Mastani's Tomb, located in the quaint village of Pabal, just 60 kms from Pune. This sacred site covers 2,000 sq ft and is enclosed by a boundary wall with three doors, featuring an elevated platform for reading namaz on the fourth side. Mastani, renowned as the second wife of Peshwe Bajirao I of the Maratha Empire, rests here. Dive into the legend where Maharaja Chhatrasal of Bundelkhand, under threat from Mohammad Khan Bangash, sought Bajirao I's aid. Grateful for his victory, Chhatrasal bestowed one-third of his kingdom and his daughter Mastani to Bajirao I. Explore this symbol of love and legacy, capturing the essence of historical architecture and Indian heritage. Connect with us on social media for more intriguing tales and historical insights.""

videos.description:

One of the many gates built within the ancient city of Mandu, the Songarh gate shaped some architectural aspects associated with the glory of the Malwa Sultanate. videos.title: Check out the architectural marvel of Hathi Mahal group in Mandu I Madhya Pradesh
videos.description:
Explore the splendour of the stunning architecture of Hathi Mahal group of monuments. If you are an archaeological enthusiast then this place is definitely for you. Have a look at this hidden gem and plan a perfect trip with your family and friends. So basically this group of monuments consists of a couple of monuments in it such as Lal Sarai, Darya khan's tomb, Darya khan's mosque.  The monuments in this region reflect the grandeur and artistic achievements of the mediaeval period.
The best time to visit this place is during monsoons and winter to witness the beauty of nature, It's a perfect serene place for all the art and history lovers also visitors can get peaceful environment here away from the hustle and hustle of city. It features massive arches, thick walls, and intricate decorations, typical of the Afghan style prevalent during the Malwa Sultanate.
Things that visitors should keep in mind- visitors should carefully observe all the intricate carving, Historical sites and monuments to understand the historical context properly, Also visitors should take care of the historical site and not throw any waste or write on the walls, As protecting and preserving the historical sites and monuments is our social responsibility as a citizen 
Easiest way to get to the site- If someone is travelling by train then the nearest railway station is Indore and from their one can hire a taxi, Also by road from Indore it takes about  hours of journey, By Ujjain it is 4\5 hours and by Bhopal it is 6/7 hours of journey 

Important tips to include in travel itinerary- Comfortable Clothing: Wear comfortable shoes and clothing suitable for walking and exploring historical sites.
Stay Options: Consider staying overnight in Mandu to fully enjoy the historical sites and the scenic beauty of the region. Hire guides: Hiring a local guide can enhance your visit by providing in-depth historical context and insights about the monuments.

videos.title: Take a look at one of the highest waterfalls of India I Meghalaya I Aerial View
videos.description:
The highest single drop waterfall in the country is situated at Nohkalikai in Cherrapunji, Meghalaya, which plunges 340 meters (1,115 ft). It is a huge natural feature which is covered with forests and often looks as being wrapped in the fog, which must make it look magical. It is called Likai Waterfall because of a tale that tells how a woman named Likai threw herself off the cliff after being caught cheating by her husband while she was dancing with another man. The viewpoint offers an extraordinary view of the waterfalls and gorges. 

The pools colored emerald right at the bottom of the falls and the surrounded cliffs. The Nohkalikai Falls in Cherrapunji is a must visit for photographers and nature lovers on their quest for the lush forests of Meghalaya. Regardless of the time being right for visiting the waterfall when you will be able to enjoy the most spectacular sight of it or the dry season when the views will be clearer, waterfall is a true discovery, which reveals the beauty of Indian North East.

A perfect destination for families, it has the added advantage of availing educational benefits through its wildlife conservation programs and information dissemination.

videos.title: kumarokum backwaters, oasis of kerela
videos.description:
"Kerala: Gods own country and a friendly oasis for those looking for a pristine environment. Located by the lake of Vembanad, Kumarakom is blessed with pleasant geographical attributes such as backwater, green fields and calm water. The backwaters here differ from those in Alleppey as these are a system of combined lagoons, lakes, and canals which also provides a very peaceful look and feel of the entire region.
However, despite the growing number of guest houses, nothing can be more effective for tourists wanting to enjoy the sights of Kumarakom than a houseboat cruise. Soar above the serene waters, coconut trees, and bright green rice paddies, and get a feel of the traditional lifestyle of this picturesque region. Staying on the houseboats are very comfortable and cherishes a modern touch to give an unforgettable trip on the lake.
They also can see many varieties of wildlife, especially the ones found at the Kumarakom Bird Sanctuary. You can also see many species of birds around this park, especially migratory birds, so it is a paradise for bird-watching enthusiasts.
To get a closer look at Kerala backwaters, Kumarakom will simply blow out your expectations.

Contact us at connect@youtellme. Ai"

videos.title: Exploring Fontainhas: The Heart of Panjim I Goa
videos.description: Fontainhas is the Latin Quarter of Panaji, Goa, famous for its bright colors, colonial architecture, and rich cultural heritage. As you meander through those tiny winding streets, you will be enveloped by Portuguese and Indian influence in the ornate balconies, red-tiled roofs, and picturesque cobblestone pathways. There are many tiny art galleries, shops selling handicrafts and souvenirs, and umbrella-covered cafes serving typical Goan cuisine. The most prominent landmarks of Fontainhas have been the Chapel of St. Sebastian and the Maruti Temple, portraying its religious diversity. Whether you are a history aficionado, an architecture enthusiast, or simply someone looking for a quiet retreat, Fontainhas offers a unique view of Goa's ebullient present and glorious colonial pastit's not to be missed by the traveller across the cultural tapestry of India's sunshine state.

videos.title: Have a look at one of the largest and most ancient museums in India which Is situated in Kolkata
videos.description:
Largest and oldest museum in India is the Indian Museum in Kolkata, welcome to our virtual tour! It was established by the Asiatic Society of Bengal in 1814 and it has a lot of historical artifacts for you to see. This museum is housed in a grand old colonial building and has six sections that deal with Art, Archaeology, Anthropology, Geology, Zoology and Economic Botany of India.

Discover its vast collection including ancient Egyptian mummy, The Ashokan Pillar and some superb Mughal paintings. Be awed by fossils of prehistoric animals, rare items from Indus Valley Civilization or beautifully carved sculptures from different periods of Indian history. Indias vast cultural as well as natural history range is represented through a wide variety of exhibits at this museum.

videos.title: Jama Masjid Ahmedabad | Juma Masjid Thazhathangady
videos.description:
Jama Masjid Ahmedabad
Jama Masjid, also known as Jumah Mosque, is a mosque in #Ahmedabad, India built in 1424 during the reign of Ahmad Shah I. Lying in the old walled city, the mosque is situated outside the Bhadra Fort area, along the south side of the road extending from Teen Darwaza to Manek Chowk.

Juma Masjid Thazhathangady
Thazhathangady Juma Masjid is a mosque situated in Thazhathangady, one of the Heritage Zones[citation needed] of #Kerala, India, near the town of Kottayam. It is one of the oldest mosques in India and is more than 1000 years old. It is famous for its richness of architecture, wood carvings, and beauty. The southern half of it is demolished and extended with iron pillars, aluminium sheets, and minars in 2012. This mosque is situated on the banks of the Meenachil river.Thazhathangady Juma Masjid is also called as the "Taj Juma Masjid". The ancestors of this Masjid came and settled in Kottayam, from different parts of Kerala. The Muslims who lived here played an active role in Freedom Struggle and other National Movements.

videos.title: Exploring one of the most beautiful museums of Meghalaya I Shad Suk Mynsiem
videos.description:
Shad Suk Mynsiem or the dance of peaceful hearts is one of the biggest annual festival of the Khasi tribe of Meghalaya in India. Known to be held in April, it is often associated with the preparation of spring and a thanksgiving dance to the Almighty. The event is a dance performance accompanied with songs and reputed rituals that represents the cultural tradition of the Khasis. Both male and female performers wrapped in traditional costumes engage in a spree of dance on the tunes of drums and pipes in Weiking, Shillong. Specifically, the festival represents the qualities of purity and fertility of the women to represent the group and also the unity of the community to embrace the ability to address the nature as well as embrace their traditional values.

videos.title: Journey through the spiritual Mhasoba Temple I Mulshi I Pune I Maharashtra.
videos.description:
Today's video is dedicated to the religious Mhasoba Devsthan temple nestled in the lovely Mulshi village near Pune in the state of Maharashtra. Situated in the background of natures beauty of Western Ghats, Mhasoba Devsthan is the temple of Mhasobaa locally worshipped deity of Dhangar community who is considered to be very protective and kind.

The temple located in a green belt area with beautiful hills and green trees in its vicinity provides tranquility to assemble in. The aura at Mhasoba Devsthan has a very simple look, yet it has a different kind of feel as it is a age old Lord Mhasoba temple. There is also the holy pond besides the several minor temples making the compound to have a divine look.

In addition to being devoted to worship, Mhasoba Devsthan is a center of native cultural interactions. The annual fair which is still on full swing is a major attraction of the temple as many devotees from the neighboring villages visit the temple to offer prayers and to witness various rituals that are performed here, to watch folk dances and movie shows in open grounds. One can easily understand it is a place of worship because the environment and feelings that resonate there are so peaceful.

Welcome to the magical world of Mhasoba Devsthan, this article explains about the religious importance, technicalities about the Mhasoba Devsthan, the serene environment located in Mulshi, Pune but worth the visit. Also make sure to like, share, and subscribe for more entertaining and enlightening Spiritual Journeys!

videos.title: Exploring the beautiful city of Ahemdabad.
videos.description:
Following are the best places to visit in ahemdabad covered in this video


The Bhadra Fort is an oldest fort, situated in the middle of the city Ahmedabad, it was constructed by Sultan Ahmad Shah I in 1411. It occupies a rather large area of the city and contains a number of constructions such as palaces, mosques, and open territories. This fort is famous for its Bhadra Kali temple with the same name of the temple the fort has got its name

Said to be also known as Gandhi Ashram, it was home to Mahatma Gandhi from 1917 till 1930.This was one of the residencies of the famous Indian leader, Mahatma Gandhi, who stayed here in between 1917 to 1930. It played a very important role and was among the principal places of the Indian freedom struggle.

The Sabarmati Riverfront is one such waterfront region close to Sabarmati River, Section of it developed for the purpose of harnessing Environmental and Recreational facilities to the city.

The ISKCON Temple in Ahmedabad is a significant spiritual center dedicated to Lord Krishna, managed by the International Society for Krishna Consciousness (ISKCON)

Ahmedabad One Mall earlier known as Alpha One Mall is one of the biggest shopping malls at Ahmedabad dealing
 in retail, food courts as well as amusement services.

Teen Darwaza, or """"Three Gates,"""" is a historical gateway situated in the old city of Ahmedabad. It was built in 1411 by Sultan Ahmed Shah and served as a royal entrance to the Bhadra Fort.

videos.title: Have a look at the most thrilling and colourful festivals of Goa.
videos.description:
Viva Carnival, one of the most thrilling and colourful festivals in Goa. So, this is held annually in February or March, and it celebrates the rich Portuguese heritage that underpinned Goa and its lively culture. But for this four-day event, the streets of Panaji, Margao, Vasco da Gama, and Mapusa turn into a blaze of hues, music, and dancethe most happening carnival of India.

Viva Carnival features a street parade, headed by King Momo, which is a mythical king of the carnival. This king leads in proclaiming the declaration of "Eat, drink, and be merry!" with parades featuring beautiful floats, heavy-costumed dancers, musicians, and other entertainers. All these create an atmosphere that surrounds this event. Participants and spectators alike are all attired colorfully to add to its vivid ambience.

Besides, it has parades, street performances with live music and dance competitions in traditional Goan folk dances like the Dekhni and Fugdi. Food stalls are set up on the streets to tout a sumptuous array of Goan delicacies, seafood, and international cuisine for feasting on a delectable treat to all senses.

Join us as we unfold the whole energy and excitement of Viva Carnival, capturing the essence of Goa's disparate cultures and traditions with a joyous spirit.

videos.title: Take a virtual tour of Amer fort, Rajasthan
videos.description:
Today we are going to see one of the biggest and the most beautiful forts in India, it is called Amer Fort and it is in Jaipur, in Rajasthan. Amer Fort was constructed in 1592 by Raja Man Singh , and has got Hindu architecture influences mingled with the pure Mughal architecture. Overlooking the vast space covering Maota Lake and hill ridges, the fort is built on a hill.  
It has some beautiful courtyards, the marvelous cutter stonework around the fort, and Palaces, namely Sheesh Mahal or the Mirror Palace and Diwan-e-Aam or the Hall for Public Durbar. Also, remember the fantastic light and sound display, which is performed at night and tells the story of the fort. Overlooking Fort tourism, Amer Fort can be reached by a jeep ride and should not be missed by any history or architecture lover.

videos.title: Our journey through kapu estuary I Mangalore
videos.description:
Lets commence our journey to Kapu Estuary, which is less known but a beautiful estuary located on the southwestern coast of India in the region of Karnataka. This is an ideal environment to combine natural and pure scenery or history and have the atmosphere of the seashore. Activities such as bird watching, self-guided tours, and fishing are perfect for a nature lover, while history lovers can take time to read some history about the place away from crowds that throng famous places. Lets dive in! 
Kapu, also spelled as Kapu, Is a small coastal town located about 13 kilometers south of Udupi in Karnataka. This picturesque estuary is formed where the river merges with the Arabian Sea, creating an unique ecosystem 

Among all objects, which can be seen in Kapu, the most significant is its landmark  a powerful lighthouse, which is situated on a rock infront of the sea. This lighthouse was constructed in 1901 during the British rule, and since then, it has had a significant assistance to different ships that required shelter for several years.

videos.title: -   | Ashtavinayak Varadavinayaka Mahad
videos.description:
On the auspicious occasion of Ganesh Utsav, we present to you a short video about Varad Vinayak Ganpati or Mahad Ganpati Temple.
 Also spelt as Varadavinayaka Mahad, it is one of the Ashtavinayak temples of the Hindu deity Lord Ganesha. It is located in Mahad samll town situated in Khalapur taluka near Karjat and Khopoli of Raigad District, Maharastra, India.

The Varadvinayak Mahad Ganpati Temple/Mandir is the Seventh Ganesha temple among Ashtavinayak to be visited during the Ashtavinayak Darshan yatra/tour. The idol at the VaradVinayak Mahad Ganpati Temple is Swyambhu murti and the temple is actually recognised as a Math.The temple is very simply designed with a tiled roof, a dome 25 feet high with golden pinnacle and a golden summit (Kalas) which has a carving of a cobra (also a deity revered by Hindus). The Temple is 8 feet long and 8 feet broad.

The original idol of Varadvinayak can be seen outside the sanctum. Since the idol was in a badly weathered condition, the temple trustees immersed that idol and consecrated a new idol in that place. However, such a decision of trustees was objected by few people and a suit was filed in the district court. Result of this case is still awaited. Now two idols, one inside the sanctum and one outside the sanctum can be seen. The sanctum made up of stone and surrounded by beautifully carved stone elephant carvings, houses the idol.

Lord Ganesha is said to reside here in the form of varada Vinayaka, the giver of bounty and success. This Ashta Vinayak shrine faces east (Purvabhimukh) and is enshrined in the sitting posture, with his trunk turned towards the left. The stone idols of Riddhi and Siddhi are seen in the sanctum. Lord Ganesha as Varad Vinayak fulfills all desires and grants all boons.

videos.title: 360 Immersive Ganesh Aarti Experience | Vighneshwar Ashtavinayak Ganpati, Ozar | Ganesh Chaturthi
videos.description: #virtualaarti #ganeshchaturthi #360 #ashtavinayak #onlineaarti Enjoy the 360 Virtual Aarti and Seek the online darshan and blessings of Lord Shri Ganesha on the auspicious occasion of Ganesh Chaturthi. Shot by Insta360 Titan 11k and GoPro max 5.6 InstaPo 2. The Vigneshwara Temple or Vighnahar Ganapati Temple of Ozar (also spelt as Ojhar or Ojzar) is a Hindu temple dedicated to Ganesha, the elephant-headed god of wisdom. The temple is one of the Ashtavinayaka, the eight revered shrines of Ganesha in Maharashtra, India. The Ganesha form worshipped here is called Vigneshwara (spelt also as Vigneshvar , Vigneshwar : "Lord of obstacles") or Vignahar (spelt also as Vignahara, "Remover of obstacles") and is associated with the legend of Ganesha defeating Vignasura, the demon of obstacles. Ganesh Chaturthi , also known as Vinayaka Chaturthi, or Vinayaka Chaviti is a Hindu festival celebrating the arrival of Lord Ganesh to earth from Kailash Parvat with his mother Goddess Parvati/Gauri. The festival is marked with the installation of Lord Ganesh's clay murtis privately in homes and publicly by Shri Bal Gangadhar Tilak popularly known as Lokmanya Tilak in Pune in the year 1893 on elaborate pandals (temporary stages). Observations include chanting of Vedic hymns and Hindu texts such as, prayers and vrata (fasting).Offerings and prasda from the daily prayers, that are distributed from the pandal to the community, include sweets such as modaka as it is believed to be a favourite of Lord Ganesh. The festival ends on the tenth day after start, when the idol is carried in a public procession with music and group chanting, then immersed in a nearby body of water such as a river or sea, called visarjan. In Mumbai alone, around 150,000 statues are immersed annually. Thereafter the clay idol dissolves and Ganesh is believed to return to Mount Kailash to Parvati and Shiva. The festival celebrates Lord Ganesh as the God of New Beginnings and the Remover of Obstacles as well as the god of wisdom and intelligence and is observed throughout India, especially in the states such as Maharashtra and Goa.

videos.title: Experience the divine aura of the Shri Shirdi Sai Baba Temple through this immersive 4K documentary.
videos.description: Gurubrahma guruvishnu gurudevo maheshwara | Guruh sakshat param brahma tasmai shri gurave namah || Om Sai Ram, a village in the Ahmednagar district, Maharashtra. It is also known as the abode of Sai Baba. Sai Baba spent sixteen years of his life here. After the completion of his divine journey, his shrine, which was previously called the Dwarkamai, is now known as the Samadhi Mandir. The residence of Sai Samadhi Mandir is nearby. Behind it, there is a neem tree, where Baba was seen for sixteen years. There is also a garden made by Baba with his own hands. Patience, faith, and perseverance. This is the residence of Sai Baba, where Baba spent sixteen years of his life. Coming here, you will experience peace and tranquility, just as Baba still resides here. Ahead of Dwarkamai, there is a courtyard where Baba used to spend his evenings. Even today, devotees come here to seek his blessings. The residence of Sai Samadhi Mandir is Hanumanji's and Malarimata's abode. Here, a saintly Muslim leader, Fakir, who was impressed by Baba's divine attributes, started calling him ""Sai"" and merged into him. And everyone belongs to one master. Sai Baba also did not differentiate based on religion or caste. That is why people from all religions come here to have Sai Baba's darshan. One of the devotees, Abdul Baba, also lived in the same residence. Thursday is known as Guruvaar. Because of this, every Thursday, a procession is organized from the Sai Baba Sansthan. This procession goes through the market, ends at Dwarkamai, and returns to the courtyard. Sai Baba, who taught people throughout his life, is still close to the hearts of many people through his service. Through the Sai Baba Sansthan, devotees receive residence, food, and free bus service. The food prepared here is also made using solar power. And the Sansthan also operates a school, college, and charitable hospital. Which benefits common people. So come and visit Sai Baba's abode, which speaks of humanity and service. Jai Sai Ram.

videos.title: Exploring one of the most popular and sensational structures of India: howrah bridge
videos.description:
Welcome to our channel! Today we decode this sensational structure transporting us into the world of Kolkata, the Howrah Bridge. Called Rabindra Setu in its formal terms, this  bridge stretches over the river Hooghly plying between Howrah and Kolkata. Design of building was done before independence and is engineering masterpiece with no nuts and bolts in it though, is consist from 26500 tones of steel fixture.

It is the longest bridge built to measure 705 meters long and 71feet wide; it can hold about 100000 vehicles and countless pedestrians every day. It not only connects two cities and effectively serves as a bridge for traffic movement but also figures prominently as a symbol of identity in films, photographs, and paintings.

videos.title: Nature's majestic wonder: Gurez, Jammu and Kashmir
videos.description:
For the next riding trip, we travelled on the roads to marvel the natural beauty of the valley called Gurez, in the state of Jammu & Kashmir. Nestled in the valley of the Himalayas in the northern state of Jammu and Kashmir is the valley of graceGurez Valley is one of the naturally blessed places that has been unheard of to many because of its seclusion and beauty. Srinagar city is the capital, which is almost 123 kilometers away from this destination Making it an undiscovered paradise for anyone who considers himself or herself a lover of nature or a tourist who seeks some form of adventure.
Next to it there is the green pasture land, the water of which is clear, and many mountains which are snowy capped are there too. The major water channel in Gurez is river Kishanganga which contributes to the natural beauty of the valley of Gurez and it is one of the most attractive places for the fisherman, besides, this has the glaciers place beside the river side. Dawar, Tulail, Habba Khatoon: The villages of the Dard-Shinas are referred as Shina community with an opportunity of enjoying freedom of being hosted and learning more of their culture which is quite different from other parts that one has visited.
So, come with me, and you can see the beauty of Gurez right from Hedbaat, the highest peak of the region to the archeologically significant forts. Experience the isolation of this protected valley and find out why any traveler who goes to Gurez must try out this natural wonder. And that brings our show for today to an end folks, please do not forget to like, share and subscribe to this channel for more traveling, especially on the sunshine interstate highways.

videos.title: Best places to visit in Manglore.
videos.description:
Welcome to Mangalore City!

Welcome to the spirit of Mangalore tourism, let us  take you to a journey through Mangalores identity and discover places that are not easily found.

Panambur Beach - Perhaps you would like to take a quite walk on the new Mangalores most admired beach. The golden sand and splendid view of the sun-setting make Panambur beach a right place for leisure and a trip of adventure. Camel cart ride by the sea side, jet skiing or just the music of the sea, there is something for everyone at Panambur Beach.

Kadri Manjunath Temple  Visit the spirituality of Kadri Manjunath Temple famous for holding the spiritual peace of more than thousand years old temple in Kadri. There is this Shiva temple that hosts marvelous bronze cast artifacts and beautiful architecture all over. Pay special attention to gardens and the holy pond that can be found in the territory of the temple.

Mangaladevi Temple  Get the religious taste of Mangalore at Mangaladevi Temple. Being one among the oldest temples in the state of Maharashtra, the temple is dedicated to Goddess Mangaladevi. This temple was sighted in the 9th century; the temple has admirable carvings, and the place has a calm ambience that anyone would expect to find in a temple.

Rosario Cathedral - Visit Rosario Cathedral, probably the largest and magnificent church in Mangalore, it is said to be among the oldest church built in Mangalore as well. This cathedrals style is Gothic and the interiors of the cathedral are adorned with stained glass paintings, and its serene environment clearly explains the religious journey of Mangalore.

Museum - Srimanthi Bai Memorial Government Museum will give you glimpse of the the bountiful cultural assets of the country. Featuring ancient coins, sculptures, paintings and other crafts this museum is home to one of the most interesting collections of the regions culture and art pieces.

Kadri Hill Park - Last but not least, one must visit Kadri Hill Park that offers Retention of trees, plants, beautiful flowers, etc. It is suitable for relaxation by taking a walk round, family outing with food and drink, beautiful flowers garden, musical fountain and site seeing of Mangalore. It is a perfect place to be placed vacant and take a brief scorn around the nature.

videos.title: Famous Kashmiri Shawls | Masterful Fabric Artisans
videos.description:
Kashmir is home to some of the most beautiful and intricate hand-embroidered shawls in the world. These shawls are made entirely by hand and can take anywhere from 6 to 36 months to complete.

These shawls are the epitome of Kashmirs rich arts and crafts tradition. They make the perfect gift for someone special or a luxurious treat for yourself.

videos.title: All you need to know about one of the most serene garden's in the paradise: Kashmir Valley
videos.description:
Welcome to the amazing tour of Shalimar Bagh, the Mughal garden in Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir! Built in 1619 by the Mughal Emperor Jahangir for his beloved wife Nur Jahan, Shalimar Bagh is a testament to their love and the magnificence of Mughal architecture. This garden is part of a larger collection of Mughal gardens in Kashmir and is famous for its Persian style.

Spread over 31 acres, Shalimar Park has elaborate lawns, terraced flower beds, fountains and shady Sycamore trees. A central canal lined with carved stones and filled with sparkling water adds to the tranquil beauty of the park. The garden is divided into three terraces and the top part is reserved for the royal family. The magnificent Diwan-e-Khas (Hall of Private Audience) and the elaborate black marble pavilion are architectural highlights.

Join us as you stroll through the stunning landscapes of Shalimar Bagh, explore the rich history, astonishing scenery and timeless beauty that continues to draw visitors. Don't forget to like, share and subscribe for a better travel experience!


Contact us on connect@youtellme.ai

videos.title: Stunning Aerial View of Rosario Cathedral, Mangalore | 4K Drone Footage | Our Lady of the Rosary
videos.description:
Discover the Rosario Cathedral, a gem of Mangalore and a beacon of peace, with our breathtaking aerial drone footage. This 16th-century Roman Catholic Church, also known as the Church of Our Lady of Rosary, boasts an awe-inspiring interior and a visually stunning exterior. The cathedral's cross and dome are not only architectural marvels but also serve as guiding landmarks for ships entering Mangalore Harbour. Rosario Cathedral is celebrated as Mangalores most distinguished Roman Catholic cathedral, attracting visitors with its serene ambiance and striking architecture. Join us on a cinematic journey above this historic sanctuary.

videos.title: River Geography Explained | Journey from Source to Sea in 360 3D VR
videos.description: Embark on a virtual 360 3D journey along a river, from its mountain origins through the plains to the sea. Experience the youthful energy of the river as it carves through rocks creating I-shaped gorges and V-shaped valleys. Watch as it matures into a meandering river in the plains, forming loop-shaped meanders and ox-bow lakes, and finally observe its slow movement in the lower course where estuaries and deltas form. This educational tour highlights the dynamic processes shaping river landscapes. Don't forget to subscribe for more immersive nature explorations

Rajdari is relatively big, a wonderful place to have a great photo-shooting and have a perfect picnic; on the other side, Devdari is much more quiet, and lonely"".

videos.title: Discovering the beauty of Meghalaya.
videos.description:
Discover the captivating charm of Shillong, the capital city of Meghalaya. Known as the 'Scotland of the East,' Shillong boasts a blend of colonial heritage and natural splendor. Wander through the bustling streets, enjoy the vibrant local culture, and marvel at the stunning landscapes. From the serene Umiam Lake to the majestic Shillong Peak, and the tranquil Ward's Lake,
Umiam Lake also locally called Barapani is a calm water. Lying at the backdrop of high hills of verdant green this beautiful lake is ideal for nature and adventure freaks. Water sports like boats, kayaking, water skiing and sight seeing can also be performed here by the visitors. It is a source of water for the area and has aquatic plants and animals inhabiting the water body. It is very quite and therefore it is appropriate for picnics,taking of group photos and even dozing off.

Shad Nongkrem Dance Festival
It is a colorful and culturally intense celebration which is regarded as the Shad Nongkrem Dance Festival of the Khasi folks in Meghalaya, India. This specific festival is a celebration for the deity Ka Blei Synshar and is celebrated in November every year to thank for the harvest and the health and welfare of the people. The main traditional dance during the festival is conducted by the young men and women in the most elaborated traditional costumes performing the Nongkrem dance. Along with the music that includes drums beats and tangmuri pipes the dance is an impressive presentation of the Khasi culture and tradition. The other event during the festival is the holi- choreography by the Syiem and the priest further making the festival to have a religious inclination.

Cherry Blossom Festival
The Cherry Blossom Festival of Shillong Meghalaya is a delightful festival of Shillong which is focused on flowering for Cherry Blossoms. Being the only festival of cherry blossoms during the autumn this festival is celebrated usually in November. People are entertained, for the city and some nearby areas are decorated with pink and white cherry blossoms. Some of them are cultural troupes, music shows, fashion shows, and food bazaar selling the local delicacies. It is the mix of qualities of nature and celebrations of culture which draws tourist around the world seeing the beauty of Shillongs cherry blossoms.

videos.description:

Built in 1942, this iconic cantilever bridge spans the Hooghly River, linking Kolkata with Howrah. Known for its massive steel structure without any nuts or bolts, it stands as the sixth-longest of its type globally. videos.title: Hyderabad's Iconic Landmarks | Rich History and Cultural Heritage | Tellme_360
videos.description:
Discover the rich history and cultural heritage of Hyderabad through its iconic landmarks.
Explore the history of Hyderabad and Secunderabad at the iconic 120 ft clock tower located in Shivaji Nagar, Secunderabad.

The Qutub Shahi Tombs in Hyderabad is a unique historical monument with Persian, Pathan, and Hindu architectural styles. The tombs are beautifully landscaped and house the entire dynasty in one spot. A must-visit destination in Hyderabad's tourist circuit, often paired with Golconda Fort.

Charminar is a historic monument and a timeless symbol of Hyderabad's rich cultural legacy, built in 1591 by Muhammad Quli Qutb Shah.

Golconda Fort is an ancient fortress complex perched on a granite hill, ruled by Kakatiya and Qutub Shahi kings.

Mecca Masjid, one of the largest and most iconic mosques in the world, is situated in the Old City of Hyderabad and was built over a period of 77 years by thousands of skilled masons.

videos.description:

Mainapi Waterfall: Located in Netravali Wildlife Sanctuary in South Goa, this magnificent cascade requires a trek of approximately 4.85 kilometers, taking around one hour to complete.
Savari Waterfall: Found in the eastern part of Goa, in the Netravali sanctuary of Sanguem taluka, this stunning location enchants visitors with its beauty. Summer treks to Savari waterfall offer a memorable experience for nature lovers.
Vainguinim Waterfall: One of Goa's best-kept secrets, this serene oasis provides a peaceful escape from bustling tourist crowds. Make sure to add Vainguinim Waterfall to your must-see list when in Goa!

videos.title: Explore the charm of Mawphlang I Meghalaya.
videos.description: Explore the charm of Mawphlang, Meghalaya which is a largely unpolluted beautiful village located in the East Khasi Hills. Based on the theme of worship, religious, and spirituality of sacred groves, makes this place attractive for tourists interested in nature and culture. It seems like a paradise with preventing deep forests filled with tall trees and delicate flowers such as the orchids also gain a glimpse of the Khasis, their culture and most importantly their rituals. Designed and nurtured by the indigenous people, perhaps the most inspiring case is the Mawphlang Sacred Forest which is one of the most bio diverse forests. Discover the many interesting geological features like stage-coach roads, hills with streams and a burst of colors on trees to compete with autumnal leaves. Here do not allow yourself to skip the beautiful living root bridges which are truly a unique example of bio-engineering. Thus, Mawphlang is not merely a place of tourists attraction; it can be named more precisely an everlasting adventure. Come be a part of this journey to one of the least explored gem of Meghalaya that is soaked in natural and cultural beauty which Mawphlang holds. For more interesting travel experiences hit like share and subscribe buttons.\nContact us on connect@youtellme.ai

videos.title: Explore Famous Dams in Maharashtra | Top Tourist Destinations | Tellme_360
videos.description:
Discover the stunning dams around Mulshi, Maharashtra, and their picturesque surroundings:
Kasarsai Dam: Located near Pune, close to Kasarsai and Kusgaon villages, this small dam is surrounded by greenery and hills. Popular activities include boating at Kasarsai Lake, where the Balaji Boating Club offers both engine and pedal boats.
Mulshi Dam: A perfect family weekend getaway near Pune, especially beautiful during the monsoon season. Visitors can enjoy trekking, bird-watching, and photography in a serene environment.
Temghar Dam: Situated on the river Muthu near Pune, this dam is a major water source for the city and offers a panoramic view of the reservoir and city. It's a popular local picnic spot.
Rihegaon Dam: Near Bhugaon and Pune, this small dam offers stunning sunsets and is a great spot for bird-watching. Easily accessible, it's the perfect weekend escape.

videos.title: Discover Goa: Must-Visit Tropical Beaches and Hidden Gems | Summertime Exploration
videos.description:
Explore Goa's coastal wonders and discover these must-visit tourist spots:
Dona Paula Beach: Known as the lovers' paradise in Goa, located 7 km from Panjim. Enjoy the stunning coastline that shimmers in the sunset. The marketplace outside the beach offers charming products like hats, feni, and hair accessories. Dona Paula is famous for its water sports adventure activities and seafood joints.

Bambolim Beach: A peaceful and secluded stretch of sand and rocks in North Goa, shaded by swaying coconut palms. Perfect for a beach picnic or quiet relaxation away from the crowds. The nearby Bambolim Beach Resort offers rooms for rent and a great restaurant serving Goan and continental cuisine.

Shiroda Beach: A popular destination for beach holidays in Siridao, Goa. The blue sea, dazzling water, and cool breeze create a beautiful atmosphere. Coconut and palm trees line the beach, adding to its beauty. The beach is also conveniently connected to major cities.

videos.title: Unveiling the Mysteries: The Monoliths of Nartiang in Meghalaya | A Cultural Journey
videos.description:
Embark on an enthralling journey to the Monoliths of Nartiang in the Jaintia Hills of Meghalaya. Explore the village of Nartiang, where ancient stone structures narrate the rich history and traditions of the region. These monoliths, with standing menhirs honoring male ancestors and flat dolmens dedicated to female ancestors, serve as a timeless tribute to the community's heritage.

Don't miss our full documentary premiering on 19th May 2023, which dives deep into the remarkable cultural heritage of this site. Join us for an immersive exploration of this historical landmark and discover the stories embedded in each stone.

videos.title: Pashmina - Threads of Glory
videos.description:
#shorts 
Pashmina - Threads of Glory
The making of Pashmina involves collecting the fine hair of the Pashmina goat, sorting raw Cashmere, spinning, weaving, and creating a world-class shawl. Indeed, the entire process is both extensive and thorough. It demands a precision that is beyond many. 
The unending love and infatuation for Kashmiri shawls were actually spread by Europeans, whose royalty was especially swooned by it. Their love for these shawls continued to span generations together, embracing every single individual, of all ages, genders, or temperaments. Kashmiri shawls were like musings for women, and their noble courts exuded the essence and timelessness of these luxury textiles. No doubt, the resplendent shawls of Kashmir are sometimes referred to as the golden fibre of Kashmir

videos.title: Discovering the Beauty of Kerala's hidden gem, Palozhukumpara Waterfall
videos.description:
Discover the hidden gem of India the  Palozhukumpara waterfall nestled in the lush green serene of Kerala, This pristine beauty is in Thiruvambady in the Kozhikode district, This waterfall is an absolutely perfect getaway for nature lovers, this place is full of greenery and beauty. One can witness the utmost beauty of this waterfall in the monsoon season.
The journey to the waterfall is full of trekking through a dense forest, the lush surroundings create a perfect setting for a relaxing day out with family and friends. Make sure to carry your own food and water, as there are limited facilities nearby.
often referred to as the ""Scotland of Asia,"" is renowned for its rolling meadows, misty hills, and serene landscapes. The Palozhukumpara Waterfall adds to the charm of this picturesque town, The name Palozhukumpara translates to a place where milk pours, aptly describing the milky white waters gushing down the cascading rocks. One should always take all the safety measures and wear comfortable clothing while planning to visit the waterfall.
Once in Vagamon, local taxis and auto-rickshaws can take you to Palozhukumpara Waterfall, which is located a short distance from the main town, Thus the nearest station is  Kottayam, about 64 km from Vagamon if someone is planning to visit by train.
The beauty of the waterfall lies in a peaceful atmosphere, the area around the waterfall is rich in flora and fauna which makes it ideal for bird watching and peaceful nature walks.

videos.title: Undavalli Caves | Vijaywada | Andhra Pradesh
videos.description:
#shorts
The Undavalli Caves date back to the 7th century BC and are prime example of rock-cut architecture. The caves are about 8 kilometres from Vijayawada and offer a unique perspective into ancient religious practices. The caves are carved out of sandstone on the side of a hill. While there are many caves, the largest is the one that is most popular for its huge monolith of Lord Vishnu in the reclining posture. The main cave is a prime example of Gupta architecture style, which concentrated on primitive rock-cut monastery cells.

videos.title: Have you been to the most popular Goa carnival? Let us take us to the virtual tour of the Festival
videos.description:
Welcome to the lively, vivacious Goa Carnival 2020! This four-day jamboree happens to be one of the most-awaited events across India and is conducted every year in the beautiful state of Goa. It showcases the rich cultural heritage of this land while radiating streaks of fun. The carnival is traced as far back as the 18th century and hence is a legacy left behind by the Portuguese. It hosts a kaleidoscope of parades, music, dances, and fun activities.

The streets of Panaji, Margao, Vasco da Gama, and Mapusa are a medley of colorful floats, exuberant costumes, and pulsating music. It is participated in by revelers worldwide who join in the festivities, dancing to the rhythms of traditional Goan music mingled with international beats. Grand parades are led by King Momo, who declares, at the commencement of the carnival, that everybody should start eating, drinking, and making merry.

Other than the parades, the Goa Carnival 2020 features multitudes of live performances by various local and international artists, energetic street plays, food stalls that give a taste of Goan delectable cuisine, and the Red and Black Dance, which culminates the festivities with its grandeur of all dressed red and black.

Join us for a thrilling journey of Goan Carnival 2020lavish traditions, exciting cultures, and that infectious energy one gets while experiencing this event. Please Like, Share, and Subscribe for more such cultural adventures!

Greetings and welcome  today we will be discussing the fabulous Ellora Caves, particularly Cut 3 in the city of Chhatrapati Sambhaji Nagar, Maharashtra. The Ellora Caves are on the list of UNESCO World Heritage site and are famous for their architecture cut in rock and carving.

This great complex includes Cut 3 that reflects the skills of Indian masters of the ancient period in terms of both art and architecture. There are many outstanding sculptures and reliefs with different gods and scenes of mythology. This cave like many other caves in Ellora depict the fusion of Hindu, Buddhists and Jainism and can give one a remarkable history of cultures of that period.

videos.title: Omkareshwar : A Spiritual Journey in 360 Degrees | 360
videos.description:
It can only be termed as a blessing by the lords and mother nature, that Omkareshwar, the sacred island, is shaped like Om - the holiest symbol of Hinduism. It is adorned with lofty hills, between which the river Narmada forms a serene pool.

A cantilever-type bridge running over river Narmada. It is a 270 ft. hanging bridge that enhances the beauty of Omkareshwar.

Out of the major places to visit in Omkareshwar, the Omkareshwar Jyotirlinga shrine tops the list. Popularly known as 'Omkar Mandhata', it is one of the 12 Jyotirlinga shrines in India. Pilgrims in unimaginable numbers visit the shrine every year, seeking the blessings of Lord Shiva.

videos.title: Lamheta Ghat Jabalpur: A Peaceful Retreat by the Narmada River
videos.description:
Lamheta Ghat is an upscale place to visit located on the bank of Narmada River in Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh. This ghat has impressed people by its calm environment and beautiful background and it is popular among those people who travel to find peace and get closer to the nature. This place is famous for the golden sizes of the sun during the sunrise and sunset as it provides one of the beauty scenes, which attract many photographers and nature lovers.  

Hindus believe that souls are cleansed of all sins while offering their final prayers on the banks of the river in the city hence the name Lamheta. With such cultural and spiritual richness, the location of Lamheta Ghat also benefits from argioura-architecture Ancient Temples nearby add to the location cultural appeal. Lying near the boat is the calm water on the ghat side where one can take a boat ride and get different views of the region. In fact, there is company of Bhedaghat and Marble Rocks that makes it a perfect point to visit for the traveler moving to Jabalpur.  

Most of the local sites offer either serenity, or spirituality or just a view to relax, With Lamheta Ghat, a visit will forever be etched in your memory. Just dont forget to take picture of its beauty while on the trip.

videos.title: Gwarighat Boat Ride Jabalpur: A Tranquil Journey on the Narmada River
videos.description:
Take a dip in the spirituality with the Gwarighat Boat Ride located at Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh on the banks of Narmada River. Gwarighat is famous for its attractive religious environment and enchanting geographic feature and thus serves as a popular tourist destination and holy place away from home.  

With the boat moving gently on murky aqua colored water, on ones side you get to see forests and leaves and on other the hills in the far background. Its even better during sunset and sunrise because the paintings of colors across the sky are seen on the plain calm river.  

Gwarighat is also a spiritual site which has attracted many spiritual people and scholars. He told my group that people visit this place to bathe on religious occasions, do puja and also attend several evening prayers, which are beautifully followed by singing of hymns and lighting lamps.  

No matter the purpose  to chase for solitude, spirituality or just a picturesque tour, the Gwarighat Boat Ride enclouded mustnt be missed out in Jabalpur. And dont forget to make an amazing number of photos and feel the quiet and spiritually rich atmosphere of this place.

videos.title: Gwarighat Aarti Jabalpur: Experience the Spiritual Vibes by the Narmada River
videos.description:
Gwarighat Aarti performed here at Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, is one of the most sacred and spiritually fulfilling events in the region. Taking place daily along the Narmada River, Aarti is an enchanting ceremony that pulls in crowed of appreciators. The Gwarighat Temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and the puja Mahotsav is performed in front of this temple. In the evening when the temple is closed for other people the noise of conch shells, drums, and bells are rung to make the environment full of devotion and free from noise. Aarti is performed with lots of energy where priests chant mantra and do puja for Lord Shiva and the sky is filled with the light of Aartis lamps. The shining lamps on water and the flowing Narmada waters complete religious beauty of the scene. Most visitors get really emotional because of the tranquility and the vibration of the holy energy in the place. If you are a traveler in Jabalpur and want to get a taste of culture or even pray, Gwarighat Aarti holds an excellent magnificent moment for everyone.
