videos.title: Embark on a 360-degree journey through the majestic Marble Rocks of Bhedaghat.
videos.description: Experience the mesmerizing beauty of the marble rocks along the graceful Narmada River in Bhedaghat, Jabalpur. These towering white formations seem to transform magically as you glide along the river. Indulge in a moonlit boat ride amidst the silver glow of the marble rocks, while the boatman weaves imaginative tales and shares insights about the surroundings. Flowing peacefully through the high marble cliffs is the tranquil Narmada, leading to the spectacular Dhuandhar Falls. Named for the misty appearance created by the powerful cascading water, the falls are most impressive during the monsoon season, resonating with a distant roar. Nearby, the magnificent 10th-century Chaunsath Yogini Temple, dedicated to goddess Durga, showcases unparalleled artistry, offering a glimpse into the past. Explore the picturesque town of Bhedaghat, where natural wonders and heritage sites blend seamlessly, promising to delight every traveler. If these enchanting attractions don't beckon you to visit Jabalpur district, what will? This content is curated for Madhya Pradesh Tourism Board and shared with global audiences via Tellme360. videos.title: India's First planned Hill Station | Lavasa | Pune
videos.description:
#shorts
Known as India's newest hill station, the Lavasa Corporation is constructing this private city. The city is a beautiful project, stylistically based on the Italian town Portofino. Spreading across 7 hills, covering an area of 25000 acres, Lavasa is a perfect blend of beauty and infrastructure.

Lavasa is a privately planned hill city located near Pune in Maharashtra. This modern day hill station is an enjoyable retreat for all its visitors and has a lot to offer to its tourists from picturesque sceneries to an extremely well-developed infrastructure including hotels, resorts, educational institutes, malls, residential property, IT companies etc. Lavasa is turning out to be a new hangout for people looking for a small trip away from the hustle and bustle of hectic city life. It is absolutely a leisure holiday destination located in the middle of lush green hills. Lavasa city is located in the Western Ghats of Maharashtra and manages to charm one with its mesmerising views. It is situated in Mose Valley near Pune at a distance of 65 Km, about an hour drive, and from Mumbai, it is approximately 200 Km away. Spread over 25,000 acres of land, it covers 65Km of lakefront that gives the whole city a mesmerising look.

videos.title: Sabarmati Ashram - Gandhi Smarak Sangrahalay#SabarmatiAshram a
videos.description:
On the occasion of Mahatma Gandhi Jayanti, we present to you aerial views of Sabarmati Ashram.

Sabarmati Ashram (also known as Gandhi Ashram) is located in the Sabarmati suburb of Ahmedabad, Gujarat, adjoining the Ashram Road, on the banks of the River Sabarmati. This was one of the many residences of Mahatma Gandhi who lived at Sabarmati (Gujarat) and Sevagram (Wardha, Maharashtra) when he was not travelling across India or in prison. He lived in Sabarmati or Wardha for a total of twelve years with his wife Kasturba Gandhi and followers, including Vinoba Bhave.

videos.description:

These temples are situated in the shaded dense forest areas of Amarkantak thereby portraying a perfect example of south eastern Madhya Pradeshs glorious historical background in terms of religions. This place is perfect for tourists, who are interested in history and spirituality and who doesnt want to visit this place where there is no hustle, bustle noise and crowd. Some of prominently famous are the temples of Lord Shiva and other Hindu gods, pilgrims go there for seeking blessings and the couples and families visit there for fulfilling their tour purposes and to see the fine architecture. Temples are holy places and therefore moving around the compound one feels the divine presence and a feeling of being overly spiritual Transcendent tower structures and rich historic architecture create the magical ambiance needed in such places. videos.title: 800 year old Tradition Kept Alive
videos.description:
#shorts 
Pandharpur Wari is an 800 year old tradition kept alive in Maharashtra, India. Warkaris (devotees) embark on a 21 day pilgrimage to Pandharpur to honor the deity Vithoba or Vitthal. It involves carrying the paduka (holy footwear) of a saint in a palkhi (palanquin), most notably of Sant (saint) Dnyaneshwar Maharaj and Sant Tukaram Maharaj , from their respective shrines to Pandharpur. Many pilgrims join this procession on foot. Warkari is a Marathi term which means "one who performs the wari or pilgrimage. 
In this video, a sea of devotees is seen as they arrive in Pune enroute their journey towards the Pandharpur wari 2022, shot by Tellme Digiinfotech Pvt. Ltd.

videos.title: Virtual tour of Immaculate Conception Church | Goa | Panaji
videos.description:
#shorts
Our lady of Immaculate Conception, Panjim, Goa.

Located in Panjim, Goa, this place of worship is as famous as it is pious!

The colonial Portuguese Baroque style church is on a hillside overlooking the city of Panjim. Built-in 1541, this popular church is considered a chapel and conducts mass every day. The church also houses the ancient bell removed from the Augustinian ruins of the Church of Our Lady of Grace in the historical city of Old Goa.

The main altar inside the church is dedicated to mother Mary with two intricately carved, gold-plated altars on either side.  The left of Jesus's Crucifixion and the right of Our Lady of the Rosary. These two are also flanked by the marble statues of St Peter and St Paul.

videos.title: Discovering the serene, Naqshband shrine I Srinagar.
videos.description:
Welcome to Naqshband Shrine, a magnificent spiritual sanctuary in the heart of Srinagar, Jammu & Kashmir. It is dedicated to one of the greatest Sufi saints, Khwaja Naqshband Sahib. Woodwork is intricately done, and magnificent carvings reflect upon the same tradition and artistic finesse in the shrine compound.
As you walk through serene courtyards and prayer halls, it will wrap you in an atmosphere of peace and devotion. It has always served as evidence of the deep-rooted spiritual traditions and cultural harmony that flourished during centuries in the Kashmir Valley.

Take a virtual tour with me to the Naqshband Shrine to learn more about its historical significance, spiritual ambiance, and, above all, the happening community that continues relishing and upholding its legacy. videos.title: Hidden gem of Monsoons | Aruvikuzhy Waterfalls | Kerala
videos.description:

Aruvikuzhy Waterfalls are among the best-hidden gems of the State and a beautiful picnic spot. Located 11 km from Kozhencherry town in Pathanamthitta district, this place comes alive during the Monsoons and is among the most oft visited spots in the area. It offers great trekking trails and one gets to see many traditional rubber plantations as well in the area.

videos.title: Kukarramath Temple Dindori: A Hidden Gem of Spirituality in Madhya Pradesh
videos.description:
Kukarramath Temple, located in the serene town of Dindori in Madhya Pradesh, is a revered spiritual site dedicated to Lord Shiva. The temple, steeped in ancient history, is known for its tranquil ambiance, making it a perfect spot for devotees seeking peace and spiritual solace. Surrounded by lush green landscapes, the temple offers a picturesque setting, enhancing its divine atmosphere. Kukarramath is famous for its architectural beauty, with intricately designed carvings and a majestic Shivlinga at its core. The temple attracts pilgrims during major festivals like Maha Shivaratri, drawing a large number of devotees who come to seek blessings. The temples rich cultural heritage and the belief that it holds divine power make it a must-visit for those exploring the spiritual landscape of Madhya Pradesh. Whether youre looking to connect with your spirituality or simply appreciate the beauty of the temple, Kukarramath promises a memorable and enriching experience.

videos.title: Bawangaja Jain Temple Barwani: Exploring the Majestic 84-Foot Statue of Lord Adinatha
videos.description:
Bawangaja Jain Temple, located in Barwani, Madhya Pradesh, is a prominent Jain pilgrimage site known for its breathtaking architecture and spiritual significance. Situated amidst the picturesque Vindhya hills, this ancient temple is dedicated to Lord Adinatha, the first Tirthankara of Jainism. The temple is famous for housing a massive 84-foot tall idol of Lord Adinatha, which is one of the largest of its kind in India. The tranquil surroundings and intricate carvings of the temple add to its grandeur, making it a peaceful haven for devotees and tourists alike. The temple complex also features several smaller shrines, beautifully crafted sculptures, and inscriptions, offering a glimpse into the rich history of Jainism. Visitors can enjoy a scenic trek up the hill to reach the temple, which provides a panoramic view of the surrounding landscape. A visit to Bawangaja Jain Temple offers both spiritual solace and a chance to admire the architectural beauty of the region.

videos.title: Begum Mahal, Mandla: Exploring the Historic Beauty of Madhya Pradesh
videos.description:
Welcome to Begum Mahal, a historic treasure nestled in the heart of Mandla, Madhya Pradesh. This majestic structure is a testament to the rich cultural and architectural heritage of the region. Built during the reign of the Gond rulers, Begum Mahal served as a royal residence, showcasing a stunning blend of Mughal and Rajput architectural styles.

The Mahal's intricate carvings, grand arches, and ornate jharokhas reflect the opulence of its era. Despite its current state of ruins, Begum Mahal continues to captivate visitors with its historical charm and tranquil surroundings.

videos.title: A journey through serene and lush green Malshej Ghat I Pune I Maharahtra
videos.description:
Welcome to Malshej Ghat, a lovely mountain pass in the Western Ghats of Pune, Maharashtra. Malshej Ghat has everything that one can and should expect from nature: charming landscapes, serene waterfalls, and rich biodiversity. Beautiful valleys covered with greenery, misty hills, and the views of these mountains from the top are some of the prime attractions in this location during monsoon season.

The Ghat is inhabited by a wide variety of flora and fauna, with many exotic species of birds, like flamingos, which migrate during the monsoons. There are several waterfalls down the hills and hence present an ideal retreat for tranquility and pace, suitable for good photography and casual spending. The historic Shivneri Fort, the birthplace of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj, is located nearby and gives this place a hint of historical importance.

For adventure sports enthusiasts, Malshej Ghat features excellent trek routes and hiking spots with good scenic viewpoints like the Harishchandra gad Fort, that offers a panoramic view of the entire place. In its cool climate and misty peaks lies an ideal retreat from the hustle-bustle of city life.

Join us as we explore Malshej Ghat, an adventure amidst nature's beauty. We will throw light on this place's hotspot, its wildlife, and the kind of serene ambiance that has topped off the must-visit destinations in Maharashtra. Real fun! Like, share, and subscribe for more fantastic travel adventures!

videos.title: Mahaganpati, Ranjangaon - Ganesh Stotra | ,  -   |
videos.description:
On the auspicious occasion of Ganesh Utsav, we present to you a short video about The Ranjangaon Ganpati temple or well know as Mahaganpati of Ranjangaon.
Located in Shirur Taluka about 51.5 km (via Pune - Ahmednagar Highway - in 1 hr 31 min) from Pune, this is the eighth temple visited by devotees who set out on the divine Ashtavinayak tour/Darshan. The idol at Ranjangaon is of Mahaganpati, the most powerful representation of Lord Ganesha. In the events or Ganesh Jayati days, lots of small shops here for shopping and the sweet Prashad (Pedha) of Lord Ganesha.

Managanpati is portrayed, seated on a lotus, flanked by his consorts Siddhi (spiritual power) and Riddhi (prosperity). The idol of Lord Ganesha is also named as 'Mahotkat', and it is said that the idol has 10 trunks and 20 hands. Mahaganpati is depicted as having eight, ten or twelve arms. It is after invoking this form of Ganpati that Shiva vanquishedthe demon Tripurasur and so he is also known as Tripurarivade Mahaganpati.

videos.title: Take a look at the rich history of Mandu I Madhya Pradesh.
videos.description:
The Central Group of Monuments in Mandu, a city located in central India, state of Madhya Pradesh, is one of the most beautiful places which still preserves the architectural masterpieces of the Malwa Sultanate. This is a world heritage site that has architectural master pieces like Jami Masjid, Hoshang Shahs Tomb, Ashrafi Mahal and more some of them represent a Hindu style and Islamic style.

Jami Masjid, Mandu

Jami Masjid is perhaps one of the largest mosques in India and seems to have been modeled on the great mosque of the Umayyads in Damascus. It has a large open yard, a spacious hall for prayers with many numbers of domes in it and the designing of the hall which shows the architectural beauty of that period.

Hoshang Shah's Tomb

This is one of the reasons why Hoshang Shahs Tomb is counted as Indias first marble mausoleum and precursor to the Tajmahal. The style of architecture of this tomb can be described as peculiar; it was constructed for the Sultan of Malwa, and near the entrance there are marble screens carved and painted in amazing detail, the dome is also very intricate, and the faade features beautiful latticework.

 Ashrafi Mahal

Ashrafi Mahal which was built as a place to construct a madarsa or an Islamic school and later as a victory pillar also forms part of the Mandus history now. However, the present structure is in ruins but the architectural shrewdness of the Malwa dynasty can be well studied from the high rising pillars and some remnants of an unfulfilled dream.

Visit these extraordinary relics and discover the history and the fantastic structures of the Mandu city.

videos.title: Journey Through Time: The Royal Enclosure of Hampi | Unveiling Indias Majestic Past 2024.
videos.description:
Immerse yourself in the rich history and architectural splendor of Hampi's Royal Enclosure, a UNESCO World Heritage site nestled in Karnataka. Join us as we unravel the secrets and stories behind this awe-inspiring archaeological treasure.

Hampi, once the capital of the Vijayanagara Empire, flourished from the 14th to 16th centuries, showcasing the pinnacle of South Indian architecture and culture. Our documentary takes you on a captivating journey through its royal quarters, ceremonial platforms, temples, and administrative buildings. Marvel at the intricate carvings, majestic pillars, and sprawling complexes that reflect the grandeur of a bygone era.

Through expert insights and historical narratives, we explore the significance of Hampi as a center of power, commerce, and culture during its golden age. Discover how its strategic location and vibrant trade routes shaped its prominence in medieval India.

Moreover, experience the spiritual essence of Hampi through its sacred temples dedicated to Hindu deities like Virupaksha, Vitthala, and Hazara Rama. These temples not only showcase remarkable craftsmanship but also serve as enduring symbols of devotion and architectural innovation.

As we delve into Hampi's past, we also reflect on its present-day cultural significance and conservation efforts. Learn about ongoing initiatives to preserve Hampi's heritage amidst modern challenges.

Join us on this educational and visually stunning journey that celebrates India's majestic past and the enduring legacy of Hampi's Royal Enclosure. Whether you're a history enthusiast, architecture lover, or simply curious about ancient civilizations, this documentary promises to captivate and enlighten. Don't miss your chance to explore Hampi's timeless allure and uncover the wonders of its royal heritage.

It demands a precision that is beyond many. \nThe unending love and infatuation for Kashmiri shawls were actually spread by Europeans, whose royalty was especially swooned by it. Their love for these shawls continued to span generations together, embracing every single individual, of all ages, genders, or temperaments. Kashmiri shawls were like musings for women, and their noble courts exuded the essence and timelessness of these luxury textiles. No doubt, the resplendent shawls of Kashmir are sometimes referred to as the golden fibre of Kashmir

videos.title: - Mahalaxmi Temple of Kolhapur
videos.description:
The Shri Ambabai/Mahalaxmi Temple of Kolhapur in Maharashtra, India, is one of the three and half Shakti Peethas listed in various puranas of Hinduism. According to these writings, a Shakti Peetha is a place associated with Shakti, the goddess of power. The Kolhapur Shakti Peetha is of special religious significance being one of the six places where it is believed that one can either obtain salvation from desires or havethem fulfilled.

Ambabai Temple (also known as Mahalaxmi Mandir) is an important Hindu temple dedicated to Goddess Lakshmi, who resides here as Supreme Mother Mahalakshmi and is worshipped by locals as Ambabai. Goddess Mahalakshmi is the consort of Lord Vishnu and it is customary among Hindus to visit Tirumala Venkateswara Temple, Kolhapur Mahalakshmi Temple and Padmavathi Temple as a yatra (pilgrimage). It is believed that visiting these temples as a pilgrimage helps achieve moksha (salvation).

videos.title: Exploring the beauty of Reva kund Group I Mandu I Madhya Pradesh.
videos.description:
Baz Bahadur Palace

The Baz Bahadur Palace is one of the exquisite monuments of the 16th century located in the center of Mandu. Constructed by Sultan Baz Bahadur, these palace has large courtyards, enrich designs and peaceful atmosphere prevailing the place. It is a historical site because of its interesting combination of Rajasthani and Mughal style of architecture. This palace indeed is a testimony of the true love story of Baz Bahadur and Rani Roopmati located on the top of the Rewa Kund.

Rani Roopmati Pavilion

This is the Rani Roopmati Pavilion which sits on a hill, and provides wide-angle view of the Narmada River and the green vegetation of the Mandu Fort. It was constructed first as a strategical post of the military but was converted into a loving couples nest by Baz Bahadur for Rani Roopmati. Due to the sophisticated design as well as location of the pavilion, it is one of the most frequented by tourists who come to explore Mandu.

Rewa Kund

Rewa Kund is an ancient water tank which is religious and historically linked with the love legend of Baz Bahadur and Rani Roopmati with being located in Mandu. This sacred tank is said to have been built to maintain water for Rani Roopmatis chhatris or pavilion. Thus, Rewa Kund still continues to be a historic and calming Shiva temple as it is set amidst historical buildings and gorgeous views.
